The paper deals with automatic synthesis of reactive programs from temporal logic specifications, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several subfields of computer science. However, based on the content of the abstract, the most likely sub-category is cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science), as the paper deals with translating LTL specifications to GR(1) acceptance conditions. Other likely sub-categories include cs.PL (Programming Languages), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory), and cs.SE (Software Engineering), as the paper also touches on topics such as automata theory, synthesis algorithms, and real-world applications.
